        "About GBG:\n\nGBG is the leading expert in global digital identity. We combine our powerful technology, the most accurate data coverage and our talented team to deliver award-winning location intelligence, identity verification and fraud prevention solutions.\n\nWith over 30 years’ experience, we bring together a team of over 1,250 dedicated experts with local industry insight from around the world to make it easy for businesses to identify and verify customers and locations, protecting everyone, everywhere from fraud.\n\nWhy you should be@GBG\n\n(With the 95% of our team members that recommend us as a great place to work)\n• We make the world a safer place\n• We trust each other and win together\n• We are local experts in a global business\n• We want you to be yourself\n• We grow when you grow\n\nAbout the team:\n\nCloudcheck – A GBG product. Cloudcheck is New Zealand’s leading Electronic Identity Verification Service. We a small close-knit team based in Auckland. Our sole focus is to work on the Cloudcheck product. The team is consists of Sales, Account Management and Product Development/Engineering, led by the founder of the original CloudCheck company.\n\nThe Role:\nAs a Java Developer/Java Software Engineer you will work closely with the Senior Developer to gather requirements, design, develop enhancements and support the products and supporting production system. It is a true all-round role for and and requires a quick learner with a good attention to detail and ability to prioritise their work. This excellent opportunity will mean that you are an important contributor to one of GBG’s leading SaaS identity products that is used by many of the region's biggest and most progressive businesses.\n\nWhat you will do:\n• Development\n• Work with the business to refine development requirements and contribute to the design the requirements\n• Deliver development requirements in a timely manner\n• Help refine and deliver new product ideas\n• Enhancement\n• Identify product and process enhancements\n• Maintenance & Support\n• Maintain & improve the stability of Cloudcheck\n• Fix bugs and release these fixes in a timely and professional manner on a schedule to suit business requirements\n• Look for processing improvements and implement where necessary\n• When escalated by the business, support external IT contacts with their IT issue\n\nWhat we're looking for\n\nEssential\n• Java web development experience JSP / tag libraries, MVC development\n• API integrations – RESTful Web Services / SOA\n• Database integrations – Hibernate, PostgreSQL\n• Ability to work independently\n• Legally entitled to work in New Zealand\n• Desire to Continually develop skills / knowledge to support your personal development\n\nDesired\n• AWS/Cloud experience\n• Auckland based\n\nBehaviours we'd like to see:\n\nTo find out more:\n\nClick here to see more about what’s important to us, including our Work When and Where You Want policy, our commitment to ESG, I&D and much more.\n\nTo chat to the Talent Attraction team and find out more about our benefits, drop an email to behired@gbgplc.com and we’ll be in touch!\n\nMake life@GBG work for you.",
